{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864345021,"sessionID":"ses_2863f59e7ffebxAKmtvX29SnpI","part":{"id":"prt_d79c0adb4001gNKGpIN7MG33ov","messageID":"msg_d79c0a704001NBICTj1lpe8PTV","sessionID":"ses_2863f59e7ffebxAKmtvX29SnpI","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_1eae1e927bd842aa886614da","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure to understand:\n1. The overall project layout and directory structure\n2. The sdk-python module structure and existing patterns\n3. Any existing CodeInterpreterClient or similar client implementations\n4. Test patterns used in the project\n5. Any existing tasks.md or similar planning documents to match format\n\nSearch thoroughly in the workspace root /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z and look for:\n- sdk-python directory\n- Any client implementations\n- Test files\n- tasks.md or similar files\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, existing patterns, and any relevant code examples.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2863f4305ffePLBUZ5Js9Ex4Is (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is my detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Structure Summary: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Overall Project Layout and Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n|-- project.md                    # Project context and architecture overview\n|-- proposal.md                   # Top-level proposal\n|-- design.md                     # Top-level design doc\n|-- delta-spec.md                 # Top-level delta spec\n|-- test_spec.md                  # TDD specification (bilingual EN/CN)\n|-- tasks.md                      # Master tasks file (AR-023: CLI invoke/status)\n|-- go.mod / go.sum               # Go module (github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube)\n|-- coverage.out                  # Go coverage output\n|\n|-- cmd/\n|   |-- cli/                      # Python CLI tool (agentcube package)\n|       |-- agentcube/            # Main Python package\n|       |   |-- __init__.py       # Exports: app, PackRuntime, BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime\n|       |   |-- cli/main.py       # Typer CLI entry point (pack, build, publish, invoke, status commands)\n|       |   |-- runtime/          # Runtime operation classes\n|       |   |   |-- __init__.py\n|       |   |   |-- pack_runtime.py\n|       |   |   |-- build_runtime.py\n|       |   |   |-- publish_runtime.py\n|       |   |   |-- invoke_runtime.py\n|       |   |   |-- status_runtime.py\n|       |   |-- services/         # Provider services\n|       |   |   |-- __init__.py\n|       |   |   |-- agentcube_provider.py\n|       |   |   |-- k8s_provider.py\n|       |   |   |-- metadata_service.py\n|       |   |   |-- docker_service.py\n|       |   |-- models/           # Pydantic models\n|       |   |   |-- __init__.py\n|       |   |   |-- pack_models.py\n|       |   |-- operations/       # Operations module\n|       |       |-- __init__.py\n|       |-- tests/                # Python test suite\n|       |   |-- __init__.py\n|       |   |-- cli/              # CLI command tests\n|       |   |-- runtime/          # Runtime class tests\n|       |   |-- services/         # Service tests\n|       |   |-- models/           # Model tests\n|       |   |-- integration/      # Integration tests\n|       |-- examples/             # Example agents\n|       |-- pyproject.toml        # Package config (agentcube, Python >=3.10)\n|\n|-- pkg/                          # Go server packages\n|   |-- apis/\n|   |   |-- runtime/v1alpha1/     # CRD type definitions\n|   |   |   |-- agent_type.go     # AgentRuntime CRD\n|   |   |   |-- codeinterpreter_types.go  # CodeInterpreter CRD\n|   |   |   |-- shared_types.go   # ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort\n|   |   |   |-- constants.go      # Annotation constants\n|   |   |-- agents/v1alpha1/      # Sandbox types\n|   |       |-- sandbox_types.go\n|   |-- workloadmanager/          # Workload Manager (control plane)\n|   |   |-- handler/              # HTTP handlers (sandbox create/delete/lifecycle)\n|   |   |-- reconciler/           # K8s reconcilers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n|   |   |-- response/             # Response helpers\n|   |-- picod/                    # PicoD code execution daemon\n|   |   |-- execute.go, auth.go, server.go, config.go\n|   |   |-- files/                # File operations (read, write, list, delete, mkdir)\n|   |-- router/                   # Session-aware HTTP router\n|   |-- store/                    # Redis/Valkey session storage\n|   |-- agentd/                   # Idle cleanup controller\n|   |-- common/types/             # Shared types\n|\n|-- client-go/                    # Go Kubernetes client library\n|   |-- clientset/\n|   |   |-- typed/runtime/v1alpha1/\n|   |       |-- client.go         # RuntimeV1alpha1Client (AgentRuntimes, CodeInterpreters)\n|   |       |-- runtime_client.go # AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient (CRUD ops)\n|   |-- informers/\n|   |-- listers/\n|\n|-- python-sdk/                   # Python SDK (spec/design only - not yet implemented)\n|   |-- spec.md                   # SDK specification (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n|   |-- design.md                 # SDK design document\n|\n|-- code-execution/               # PicoD spec/design\n|   |-- spec.md\n|   |-- design.md\n|\n|-- changes/                      # Change request directories (AR-001 through AR-027)\n|   |-- AR-XXX/\n|       |-- proposal.md\n|       |-- design.md\n|       |-- delta-spec.md\n|       |-- tasks.md\n|\n|-- ci-cd/, deployment/, session-routing/, session-store/,\n    idle-cleanup/, integrations/, sandbox-orchestration/\n    # Each contains spec.md and/or design.md\n```\n\n### 2. SDK-Python Module Structure and Existing Patterns\n\nThe `python-sdk/` directory currently contains **only specification and design documents** -- no actual Python code yet. The SDK is planned as a separate package named `agentcube-sdk` (distinct from the CLI's `agentcube` package).\n\n**Planned SDK Package Layout** (from `python-sdk/design.md`):\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`) |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports: `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` class |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports: `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session()` helper with HTTPAdapter |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file()` helper |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger()` helper |\n| `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty module marker |\n\n**Key Configuration Pattern**: No single Configuration class. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed:\n- `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var (required)\n- `workload_manager_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n- `auth_token` from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- Default timeouts: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- Connection pooling: `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n### 3. Existing CodeInterpreterClient and Similar Client Implementations\n\n#### A. Go CodeInterpreterClient (`client-go/clientset/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n\nThis is a **Kubernetes-style CRUD client** for the CodeInterpreter CRD:\n\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreterClient struct {\n    store *ObjectStore\n    ns    string\n}\n// Methods: Create, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, Get, List, Watch, Patch\n```\n\n#### B. Python InvokeRuntime (`cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n\nA CLI runtime class for invoking deployed agents:\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"): ...\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict, headers: Optional[Dict]) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, ...): ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(self, ...): ...\n```\n\nUses `httpx.AsyncClient` for HTTP calls, `MetadataService` for workspace metadata.\n\n#### C. Python StatusRuntime (`cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"): ...\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict: ...\n```\n\nUses `AgentCubeProvider` and `KubernetesProvider` for K8s interactions.\n\n#### D. Planned SDK Clients (from spec/design docs)\n\n**CodeInterpreterClient** (high-level facade):\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(self, name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=3600,\n                 workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, auth_token=None,\n                 verbose=False, session_id=None): ...\n    def __enter__(self): ...\n    def __exit__(self, ...): ...\n    def stop(self): ...\n    def execute_command(self, command, timeout=None) -> str: ...\n    def run_code(self, language, code, timeout=None) -> str: ...\n    def write_file(self, content, remote_path): ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path, remote_path): ...\n    def download_file(self, remote_path, local_path): ...\n    def list_files(self, path=\".\"): ...\n```\n\n**ControlPlaneClient** (Workload Manager API):\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def create_session(self, name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600) -> str: ...\n    def delete_session(self, session_id) -> bool: ...\n    def close(self): ...\n```\n\n**CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** (Router data plane):\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def execute_command(self, command, timeout=None) -> str: ...\n    def write_file(self, content, remote_path): ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path, remote_path): ...\n    def download_file(self, remote_path, local_path): ...\n    def list_files(self, path=\".\"): ...\n    def close(self): ...\n```\n\n**AgentRuntimeClient** and **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** follow similar patterns.\n\n#### E. Exception Hierarchy (planned):\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception): ...\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None): ...\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError): ...\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError): ...\n```\n\n### 4. Test Patterns Used in the Project\n\n**Test Framework**: pytest with pytest-mock, pytest-asyncio, pytest-cov\n\n**File Naming**: `test_<module>.py` in `tests/` subdirectories mirroring source structure\n\n**Test Organization**: Class-based grouping with descriptive class names:\n```python\nclass TestInvokeRuntime_Constructor:\n    def test_default_values(self) -> None: ...\n    def test_custom_values(self) -> None: ...\n\nclass TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeAgentCube:\n    def test_invoke_agentcube_provider(self, workspace_with_published_metadata, mock_httpx_client): ...\n```\n\n**Fixture Patterns**:\n- Parameterized fixtures for different configurations (`runtime`, `runtime_verbose`, `runtime_k8s`)\n- `tmp_path`-based workspace fixtures that create temporary directories with `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- Mock fixtures using `mocker.patch()` for external dependencies (httpx, K8s providers)\n\n**Example fixture** (from `test_invoke_runtime.py`):\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_published_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\"agent_name: test-agent\\n...\")\n    return ws\n```\n\n**Mocking patterns**:\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_httpx_client(mocker):\n    mock_response = MagicMock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {\"output\": \"hello world\"}\n    mock_response.raise_for_status.return_value = None\n    mock_client = MagicMock()\n    mock_client.__aenter__ = AsyncMock(return_value=mock_client)\n    mock_client.__aexit__ = AsyncMock(return_value=None)\n    mock_client.post.return_value = mock_response\n    mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\", return_value=mock_client)\n    return mock_client\n```\n\n**Go tests** use standard `*_test.go` files with `go test ./...`.\n\n### 5. Tasks.md Format and Planning Documents\n\n**Master tasks file** (`/tasks.md`) format for AR-023:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-023: CLI invoke/status commands -- Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Task Title\n\n- [ ] Specific subtask description\n- [ ] Another subtask\n- [ ] Write test: test description\n\n## T-2: Another Task Title\n\n- [ ] ...\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1  -- T-2 -- T-5 -- T-6\n       |         |\n       |         -- T-4 --\n       |\n       -- T-3 --\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-1, T-7 | None |\n| G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11 | T-1 |\n```\n\n**AR-027 tasks.md** (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) is a **template/stub** with TODOs:\n```markdown\n# AR-027 -- SDK CodeInterpreterClient -- Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-027/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-027/design.md`, `changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. <!-- TODO: Task title -->\n<!-- TODO: Task description -->\n- [ ] 1.1 <!-- TODO -->\n**Verification:** <!-- TODO: Verification command -->\n```\n\n**AR-027 delta-spec.md** is **fully detailed** with 292 lines of requirements covering:\n- CodeInterpreterClient initialization (env vars, defaults, validation)\n- Session lifecycle (create, reuse, context manager, stop cleanup)\n- Data plane initialization (success, failure with rollback)\n- Command execution (timeout handling, exit code errors, list commands)\n- Code execution (python/python3/py aliases, unsupported language errors)\n- File operations (write, upload multipart, download stream, list)\n- HTTP client configuration (connection pooling, base URL construction)\n- Timeout defaults (5.0s connect, 120s read, +2.0s buffer for execute)\n- Exception hierarchy (AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError)\n- Logging (verbose mode, default INFO level)\n- Public API surface (__all__ exports)\n- File change matrix (13 files to create)\n\n**Key HTTP API Contracts** (from specs):\n\n| Client | Method | Endpoint | Body |\n|--------|--------|----------|------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}` |\n| ControlPlaneClient | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | -- |\n| DataPlaneClient | POST | `api/execute` | `{command: [...], timeout: \"Ns\"}` |\n| DataPlaneClient | POST | `api/files` (JSON) | `{path, content: base64, mode: \"0644\"}` |\n| DataPlaneClient | POST | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}, data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n| DataPlaneClient | GET | `api/files/{path}` | stream=True |\n| DataPlaneClient | GET | `api/files?path=.` | query param |\n\n**Session header**: `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) on all data plane requests.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2863f4305ffePLBUZ5Js9Ex4Is","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775864167672,"end":1775864345018}}}}
