{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864444189,"sessionID":"ses_2863f59e7ffebxAKmtvX29SnpI","part":{"id":"prt_d79c3a361001ONNYRvNgabn2yi","messageID":"msg_d79c399ad001kIgRR09OhKgPy3","sessionID":"ses_2863f59e7ffebxAKmtvX29SnpI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_0afac2f9568b4f778130be78","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-027/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-027/design.md`, `changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Package scaffolding and configuration\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with package name `agentcube-sdk`, Python >=3.10, dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`)\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` as empty module marker\n- [ ] Write test: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` succeeds\n- [ ] Write test: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` succeeds\n- [ ] Write test: `agentcube.__all__` contains exactly `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n- [ ] Write test: `agentcube.clients.__all__` contains exactly `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_import\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-2: Exception hierarchy\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n- [ ] Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` as base class with docstring\n- [ ] Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` with `__init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None)` and message format `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n- [ ] Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)` with docstring `\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"`\n- [ ] Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)` with docstring `\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"`\n- [ ] Export all exceptions from `agentcube.exceptions`\n- [ ] Write test: `CommandExecutionError` has `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` attributes\n- [ ] Write test: `CommandExecutionError` message includes exit code and stderr\n- [ ] Write test: all custom exceptions are catchable as `AgentCubeError`\n- [ ] Write test: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` have correct docstrings\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_exception\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-3: Utility helpers (http, utils, log)\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/http.py` with `create_session()` helper\n- [ ] Implement `create_session()` to return `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` mounted for `http://` and `https://`\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/utils.py` with `read_token_from_file(path)` helper\n- [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file(path)` to read file content and strip whitespace; return `\"\"` if file does not exist\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/log.py` with `get_logger(name, verbose=False)` helper\n- [ ] Implement `get_logger()` to set level to `DEBUG` if `verbose=True`, else `INFO`\n- [ ] Write test: `create_session()` returns session with correct adapter config\n- [ ] Write test: `read_token_from_file()` returns token content when file exists\n- [ ] Write test: `read_token_from_file()` returns `\"\"` when file does not exist\n- [ ] Write test: `get_logger(verbose=True)` sets DEBUG level\n- [ ] Write test: `get_logger(verbose=False)` sets INFO level\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_utils\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-4: ControlPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__(self, workload_manager_url=None, auth_token=None, timeout=None, verbose=False)`\n- [ ] Resolve `workload_manager_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var; raise `ValueError` if neither provided\n- [ ] Resolve `auth_token`: use arg, or read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, or `\"\"`\n- [ ] Create session via `create_session()` with default headers `Content-Type: application/json` and `Authorization: Bearer {token}` if token is non-empty\n- [ ] Set default timeout tuple `(5.0, 120)` if not provided\n- [ ] Implement `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` → POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`, return session ID from response\n- [ ] Implement `delete_session(session_id)` → DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`, return bool\n- [ ] Implement `close()` to close the session\n- [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor resolves `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` from env var\n- [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no URL provided\n- [ ] Write test: auth token from service account file when file exists\n- [ ] Write test: auth token empty when SA file missing\n- [ ] Write test: `create_session` POSTs correct body and returns session ID\n- [ ] Write test: `delete_session` DELETEs correct URL and returns bool\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` closes session without error\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_control_plane\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-5: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__(self, session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url=None, timeout=None, verbose=False)`\n- [ ] Construct `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` if not provided\n- [ ] Create session via `create_session()` with default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (lowercase)\n- [ ] Set default timeout tuple `(5.0, 120)` if not provided\n- [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` → POST `api/execute` with body `{\"command\": command, \"timeout\": \"{timeout}s\"}`, return stdout from response\n- [ ] Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` → POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": <base64-encoded>, \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n- [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → POST multipart to `api/files` with `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`\n- [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` (where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`), write response content to `local_path`\n- [ ] Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` → GET `api/files` with query parameter `path={path}`, return response\n- [ ] Implement `close()` to close the session\n- [ ] Write test: constructor constructs `base_url` from `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor uses explicit `base_url` when provided\n- [ ] Write test: session has `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command` POSTs correct body with default timeout `120s`\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command` POSTs correct body with custom timeout\n- [ ] Write test: `write_file` POSTs JSON with base64-encoded content\n- [ ] Write test: `upload_file` POSTs multipart with correct fields\n- [ ] Write test: `download_file` GETs with stream and writes to local path\n- [ ] Write test: `list_files` GETs with query param `path=.`\n- [ ] Write test: `list_files` GETs with query param `path=/tmp`\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` closes session without error\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-6: CodeInterpreterClient initialization and session lifecycle\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__(self, name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=3600, workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, auth_token=None, verbose=False, session_id=None)`\n- [ ] Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var; raise `ValueError` if neither provided\n- [ ] Initialize `cp_client` (ControlPlaneClient) with `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=(5.0, 120)`, `verbose`\n- [ ] If `session_id` not provided, call `cp_client.create_session(name, namespace, ttl=ttl)` and store returned session ID\n- [ ] If `session_id` provided, use it directly without calling `create_session`\n- [ ] Call `_init_data_plane()` to initialize `dp_client`\n- [ ] Implement `_init_data_plane()`: construct `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name=name`\n- [ ] Implement data plane init failure rollback: if `session_id` was created (not provided) and `_init_data_plane()` raises, log warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n- [ ] If `session_id` was provided and `_init_data_plane()` raises, do NOT delete session, just re-raise\n- [ ] Write test: constructor with all defaults uses env `ROUTER_URL`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no `router_url` arg or env var\n- [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit config sets all fields correctly\n- [ ] Write test: session creation on init when `session_id` not provided\n- [ ] Write test: session reuse when `session_id` is provided (no `create_session` call)\n- [ ] Write test: data plane init failure with created session triggers rollback (delete + re-raise)\n- [ ] Write test: data plane init failure with provided session does NOT delete session\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_code_interpreter_init\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-7: CodeInterpreterClient context manager and stop\n\n- [ ] Implement `__enter__()` to return `self`\n- [ ] Implement `__exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)` to call `stop()` and return `None` (do not suppress exceptions)\n- [ ] Implement `stop()` to close `dp_client`, delete control plane session if `session_id` is set, close `cp_client`\n- [ ] Implement `stop()` idempotency: safe to call multiple times without errors\n- [ ] Write test: `__enter__` returns `self`\n- [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with no exception calls `stop()`\n- [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with exception calls `stop()` and does not suppress exception\n- [ ] Write test: `stop()` closes dp_client, deletes session, closes cp_client\n- [ ] Write test: `stop()` called twice does not raise error\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager or test_stop\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-8: CodeInterpreterClient command execution\n\n- [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n- [ ] If `command` is a string, convert to list `[command]`\n- [ ] Default timeout to `120` if not provided\n- [ ] Call `dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout=timeout)` with HTTP read timeout = `timeout + 2.0` buffer\n- [ ] Parse response: if `exit_code != 0`, raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`\n- [ ] Return stdout from response\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` POSTs with body `{\"command\": [\"echo hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and returns stdout\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with `timeout=30.0` sends `\"timeout\": \"30s\"` and HTTP read timeout is `32.0`\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with `timeout=None` defaults to `120s` and HTTP read timeout is `122.0`\n- [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with list `[\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]` sends list in body\n- [ ] Write test: response with `exit_code != 0` raises `CommandExecutionError` with correct attributes\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_execute_command\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-9: CodeInterpreterClient code execution\n\n- [ ] Implement `run_code(language, code, timeout=None)` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n- [ ] Support language aliases: `python`, `python3`, `py` → write `.py` file and execute `python3 <file>`\n- [ ] Generate timestamped filename (e.g., `/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py`)\n- [ ] Call `write_file(content, remote_path)` to write code to remote file\n- [ ] Call `execute_command(f\"python3 {remote_path}\", timeout=timeout)` to run\n- [ ] Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n- [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hi')\")` writes `.py` file and executes `python3 <file>`\n- [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"python3\", ...)` treated as Python\n- [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"py\", ...)` treated as Python\n- [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"java\", ...)` raises `ValueError` for unsupported language\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_run_code\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-10: CodeInterpreterClient file operations\n\n- [ ] Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` → delegate to `dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)`\n- [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → delegate to `dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n- [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → delegate to `dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)`\n- [ ] Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` → delegate to `dp_client.list_files(path)`\n- [ ] Write test: `write_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n- [ ] Write test: `upload_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n- [ ] Write test: `download_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n- [ ] Write test: `list_files` delegates to dp_client with default path `.`\n- [ ] Write test: `list_files` delegates to dp_client with custom path `/tmp`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_file_ops\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-11: AgentRuntimeClient stub\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class skeleton with `__init__` and docstring\n- [ ] Write test: `AgentRuntimeClient` can be imported and instantiated\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_stub\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-12: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient stub\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class skeleton with `__init__` and docstring\n- [ ] Write test: `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` can be imported and instantiated\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_data_plane_stub\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-13: Logging configuration\n\n- [ ] Integrate `get_logger()` into `CodeInterpreterClient` constructor based on `verbose` parameter\n- [ ] Add debug-level logging for session creation, data plane init, command execution, file operations\n- [ ] Add warning-level logging for data plane init failure rollback\n- [ ] Write test: `verbose=True` enables debug logging\n- [ ] Write test: `verbose=False` sets INFO level (no debug output)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_logging\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-14: Integration tests\n\n- [ ] Write integration test: full session lifecycle with context manager (create → execute → cleanup)\n- [ ] Write integration test: command execution with mocked data plane (mock `requests.Session`)\n- [ ] Write integration test: file upload/download with mocked data plane\n- [ ] Write integration test: session reuse with provided `session_id`\n- [ ] Write integration test: data plane init failure triggers session cleanup\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_integration\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n\n- [ ] `ruff check python-sdk/agentcube/` — no violations\n- [ ] `mypy python-sdk/agentcube/` — no type errors\n- [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` — all pass\n- [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n\n**Verification:** Run all lint/typecheck/coverage commands\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1  ──┬── T-2 ──┬── T-4 ──┬── T-6 ──┬── T-7\